Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a medium #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to pot and keep covered off heat until ready to mash in Step 6.

While potatoes cook, heat a medium dry #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Drain @corn{1%unit}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for bacon over high heat. Add corn and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and lightly charred in spots, ~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a small #bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season with salt and pepper. Heat pan used for corn over medium-high heat. Once hot, add a drizzle of @cooking oil{}. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wash out pan.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in pan used for corn over medium heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Sprinkle with @flour{2%tablespoon} and stir vigorously to combine.

Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit} and @water{1%cup}; bring to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> If the gravy is too thick, add more water a splash at a time.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Use pan used for steak here.

To pot with potatoes, add one packet of @sour cream{4.5%tablespoon} and @butter{2%tablespoon}. Mash until smooth and creamy with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.

> If you like truffle, feel free to swap in the truffle butter for the plain butter and skip serving it on the side!

== Assembly ==

Serve mashed potatoes, bacon, green beans, corn, scallion greens, gravy, @crispy fried onions{1%unit}, @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}, @truffle butter{2%tablespoon}, and remaining sour cream family style for everyone to build their own mashed potato bowls.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Serve alongside mashed potato bar.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.